OL,3,CResident doctors in England to strike
OL,4,Cfor six days
OL,6,FIt comes after an offer from the
OL,7,FGovernment was rejected by the British
OL,8,FMedical Association's (BMA) resident
OL,9,Fdoctors committee.
OL,11,FThe proposal, published by Health
OL,12,FSecretary Wes Streeting last month,
OL,13,Fincluded a 4.9% increase in average
OL,14,Fbasic pay from 2026 to 2027.
OL,16,FAccording to Mr Streeting, this would
OL,17,Fhave left resident doctors 35.2%
OL,18,Fbetter off than four years ago.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1775653863
OL,3,CResident doctors in England to strike
OL,4,Cfor six days
OL,6,FThe proposal also included an offer of
OL,7,F1,000 extra training places, although
OL,8,Fthat was taken off the table last
OL,9,FThursday, with the Department of
OL,10,FHealth and Social Care saying it was
OL,11,Fno longer "financially or
OL,12,Foperationally" possible as the NHS
OL,13,Fprepares to deal with the fallout from
OL,14,Findustrial action.
OL,16,FHealth commentators have said that
OL,17,Fstrikes can cost up to #300 million
OL,18,Feach time.
OL,26,@sD@KOUtD@NO]
